'''''The Little Lost Bantha Cub''''' was a [[Youngling/Legends|children's]] [[Book/Legends|story]] favored by [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]], [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], and [[Anakin Solo]], usually presented by [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]]. However, the children preferred the story when read by their [[Parent/Legends|father]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]].

The story is incorrect in that a young [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]] would be referred to as a calf, not a cub.

==Text==
:''After the sandstorm that drove him from home, the little lost [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]] cub wandered alone''.

:''So he walked, and he walked through the desert heat till noon, when he found a [[Jawa/Legends|Jawa]] [[Sandcrawler/Legends|sandcrawler]] upon a sandy dune''.

:'' "I am lost," said the bantha cub, "please help me find my herd," but the little Jawas shook their heads and gave their final word''.

:''So he walked, and he walked till he met a shiny [[Droid/Legends|droid]]. After being by himself so long the cub was overjoyed''.

:'' "I am lost," said the [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]] cub, "please help me find my herd." ''
:''"I am not programmed to help you," said the droid, "Don't be absurd" ''.

:''The droid kept walking straight ahead, not looking left or right; the [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]] cub just watched until the droid went out of sight''.

:''So he walked, and he walked till the suns were almost setting. He had been outside so long, he couldn't help but sweating''.

:''But then on the other side of a cliff he saw a [[Moisture farm/Legends|moisture farm]],with a few moisture vaporators, sticking up like arms''.

:''"I am lost," said the bantha cub, "please help me find my herd." "Yes, you must be reunited with your family", the moisture farmer concurred.''

:''"However, I cannot help you find your way, for I am at my moisture farm and here I must stay" ''.

:''So he slept, and he slept till it was early in the morning. He was woken by the bright suns, which rose without a single warning''.

The cub's adventures continue with an encounter with a [[Krayt dragon/Legends|Krayt dragon]].

:'' 'I will eat you,' purred the dragon, then he lunged with snapping jaws! So the bantha cub ran without the slightest pause.''

The cub then finds a tribe of [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Sand people]] who reunite him with his parents and his herd.

